{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00415/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00415"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:04:15"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man and woman sit at a breakfast table. The woman offers a basket of pastries to the man, who is sketching."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00415","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00415"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/canvas/1/9613ce98-3cd7-479d-8648-667fa114d0ba","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:23:24.770Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The wallpaper in the dining room (“Fruit”) is derived from a William Morris design from 1866 that features pomegranates, peaches, oranges, and lemons (<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW1349036 BCX0\" href=\"https://filmandfurniture.com/2018/07/wondrous-wallpaper-phantom-thread/\"><u>#FFFind, 2018</u></a>)—another example of the film’s prominent food motif. The combination of sweet fruits (pomegranates and peaches) and sour fruits (oranges, lemons) well represents Reynolds and Alma’s dynamic: a combination of tender love and bitter resentment. Morris was a British artist, textile designer, and poet associated with the Arts and Crafts movement. The Arts and Crafts movement, largely active in Britain at the end of the nineteenth century, sought to reclaim and elevate design and handicraft traditions amidst rapid industrial development and the rise in reproductive technologies. In many senses, the movement parallels Reynolds’s investment in the laborious and detailed art of creating couture garments.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00415/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:940.8662280701755,25.054824561403528,215.47149122807002,309.9780701754387"}}}]}]}]}